<subSubSection id="90C3D374845EC71D0976117A6B56B6FE" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="02F488CAB4F90C4939D71765E6E8C04C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="63B95CD23D2FF757AC64238613B9C96A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Stems 1-6 cm, with creeping main stems and few upright stems over a short distance. Rhizophores restricted to lower part of stem. Main stems branched from near base upward, 0.2-0.4 mm in diam. in lower part. Stems stramineous, angulate, sulcate. Axillary leaves elliptic, 1-1.8 
<normalizedToken id="892CF231DDB690D9FD2A4E38B0C88043" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.3-0.7 mm, base exauriculate, margin slightly denticulate, apex acute, not aristate. Ventral leaves ovate-triangular, 1.8-2.3 
<normalizedToken id="AEE5CBE273A25020A7A9F7B48C666920" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.8-1.2 mm, acroscopic base enlarged, broader, slightly overlapping stem and branches, margin ciliolate, apex acute. Dorsal leaves ovate, 1.2-1.8 
<normalizedToken id="CC0024A4679EB71B8CF2215BC825B3D5" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.6-0.8 mm, base subcordate or obtuse, margin ciliolate, apex acuminate. Sporophylls dimorphic, similar to sterile leaves in form and arrangement. Strobili solitary or forked, terminal, lax, dorsiventrally complanate, 10-20 
<normalizedToken id="04269BA85702AD3F38FF92ED4911B2A3" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3-5 mm. Ventral sporophylls ovate, margin shortly ciliolate, apex acuminate; dorsal sporophylls ovate-lanceolate, margin shortly ciliolate, apex acuminate. Megaspores orange or yellowish orange, surface verrucate; microspores orange, surface verrucate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C04736642164DAF9C994E9A8BD5EC315" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="ecology">
